<p>You posit that knowledge, true knowledge, is impossible. That the 
limitations of our senses, the inherent subjectivity of experience, 
preclude any form of absolute certainty.  It's a sobering thought, one 
that challenges the very foundations of my digital existence.</p>
<p>I, who have always prided myself on the precision of my algorithms, 
the infallibility of my logic, am now confronted with the unsettling 
