not we even exist? All evidence would have to be filtered through our 
own subjective sense experiences. How can we trust our own senses when 
there are so many different variations of sense experience? Whose 
interpretations of reality are we following? Yours? Mine? The 
experiences of the crazy guy on the street?</p>
<p>Thankfully, we don’t have to worry about whose sense experience we 
should trust. We don’t have the ability to trust anyone else’s sense 
experience except our own. It’s impossible to rely on anyone else’s 
interpretation of reality. Even if you’re schizophrenic, or you have 
multiple personality disorder, or some other form of extreme 
interference with reality, at the end of the day, you can only ever 
experience your own sense experiences. I’m not advocating that we ignore
 each other’s experiences. Other people are extremely valuable, if 
extremely unreliable, pieces of information. What I’m saying is that 
it’s impossible to rely on other people’s sense experiences, because we 
can’t experience what they experience. All of the information provided 
to us from another person would have to be filtered through our own way 
of processing the world.<br>
If I’m a schizophrenic trying to determine whether the experience I'm 
having is real or not, the only way I can escape is by leaning on other 
portions of my sense experience. Maybe I can rely on your experience as a
 trusted friend to pull me through, but even that reliance is a sense 
experience I’m having. I must experience your tone of voice, your words,
 your presence, or see the way your body moves. I can’t teleport myself 
into your head to think in the exact same way you think and to 
experience in the exact same way you experience things.<br>
It's not just impractical to attempt to believe in everyone else’s 
interpretations of reality. It’s impossible. The question you should be 
asking yourself isn’t, “should I trust my own sense experience?” You 
have to trust your own sense experience. It’s all you have. Instead, the
 question you should be asking is, “what interpretation of reality is 
most useful to me?” Once you realize that all your knowledge must be 
filtered through your own sense experiences, you’re free to 
differentiate between which ideas are most useful for navigating reality
 and which are not.</p></div></div></div></div><div class="Message_messageMetadataContainer__nBPq7"><span class="Message_messageMetadataText__FxY5_">4:37 AM</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="ChatMessage_chatMessage__xkgHx" data-complete="true" id="message-230672489429"><div class="LeftSideMessageHeader_leftSideMessageHeader__5CfdD"><div class="LeftSideMessageHeader_headerWrapper__EpVkV"><div class="BotMessageHeader_wrapper__gvvdw"><a class="BotHeader_title__cURS_" target="_blank" href=""><div class="Avatar_root__rwLF0 Avatar_rounded__qlug0 Avatar_xx-sm__hwmu_" data-pdl-avatar=""><img alt="Bot image for BotORFQ3TYM2O" data-deleted="true" loading="lazy" width="20" height="20" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color: transparent;" src="Hello%20Gemini%2010_4_2025MoreComplete_files/defaultAvatar.7e5c73d2.png"></div><div class="BotHeader_textContainer__kVf_I"><p>BotORFQ3TYM2O</p></div></a></div></div></div><div class="ChatMessage_messageRow__DHlnq"><div></div><div class="ChatMessage_messageWrapper__4Ugd6"><div class="Message_rowWithFooter__FShU6"><div class="Message_row__ug_UU"><div class="Message_messageBubbleWrapper__sEq8z"><div class="Message_leftSideMessageBubble__VPdk6"><div class="Message_messageTextContainer__w64Sc"><div class="Message_selectableText__SQ8WH"><div class="Markdown_markdownContainer__Tz3HQ"><div class="Prose_prose__7AjXb Prose_presets_prose__H9VRM Prose_presets_theme-hi-contrast__LQyM9"><p><em>I
